cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a machine learning approach to learn compositional Koopman operators using graph neural networks. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The experiments involve manipulating ropes and controlling soft robots, indicating a robotics application. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses control synthesis using the learned dynamics, which falls under the systems and control category. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a data-driven approach to system identification and control synthesis, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although not the main focus, the paper uses visual input to encode the state of the system, which could potentially fall under computer vision.
